Case called at 1:05pm [mo]
Defendant Andrew T Bauer in court with Attorney David Robert Westrick.   ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.


The Defense admits service of Amended Criminal Complaint

Maximum penalties recited; Constitutional rights reviewed; pleas of " Guilty " entered on Counts #1, #2, #3, #4 and #5 of the Amended Criminal Complaint; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Defendant guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

The Court notes it has signed the Order to Disperse Restitution
Sentencing arguments given by Counsel
Statement made by Mr. Bauer 

On Counts #1, #2, #3, #4 and #5 of the Amended Criminal Complaint, the Court withholds sentence, and places Defendant on Probation for 1 year, with conditions:

--Mr. Bauer shall not endorse any check in a name other than his own, even if given permission 
--to undergo any assessment, treatment or counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to maintain employment as approved by the Agent
--On Count #1: to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 DNA surcharge
--On Count #2: to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 DNA surcharge
--On Count #3: to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 DNA surcharge
--On Count #4: to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 DNA surcharge
--On Count #5: to pay costs of $243 plus the $200 DNA surcharge
--to provide DNA sample to designee upon demand
